---
# Enable everything, then subtract checks that are noisy, stylistic,
# duplicated across alias families, or fundamentally hostile to a 2D
# game engine port (C arrays, pointer arithmetic, magic tuning numbers).
#
# Disabled categories — and why:
# * readability-identifier-length: math/graphics code uses x, y, dx, i.
# * readability-magic-numbers / cppcoreguidelines-avoid-magic-numbers:
#   game tuning constants are everywhere; extracting them gains no real
#   safety.
# * modernize-use-trailing-return-type: cosmetic; LLVM, Qt, KDE,
#   Chromium all disable it.
# * *-braces-around-statements, readability-math-missing-parentheses,
#   readability-implicit-bool-conversion: style preferences.
# * portability-avoid-pragma-once: we deliberately use #pragma once.
# * misc-include-cleaner: high false-positive rate against SDL/cereal.
# * bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters: famous false-positive generator.
# * performance-enum-size: pedantic; enum layout changes can break
#   serialization compatibility.
# * cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-* / -pro-type-reinterpret-cast /
#   -pro-type-vararg / -avoid-c-arrays / -macro-* / -owning-memory /
#   -non-private-member-variables-in-classes /
#   -avoid-const-or-ref-data-members / -avoid-non-const-global-variables:
#   fight C-array, macro and free-function code that a Liero port can't
#   avoid.
# * hicpp-signed-bitwise / hicpp-no-array-decay / hicpp-vararg: trigger
#   on every SDL enum bitmask op and C-interop boundary.
# * hicpp-* and modernize-* aliases of checks already enabled via
#   modernize-* or cppcoreguidelines-*: removed to stop double-counting.
# * misc-non-private-member-variables-in-classes: the options don't do
#   anything (kept from the original config).
# * modernize-use-nodiscard: too aggressive, attribute is situationally
#   useful (kept from the original config).
# * abseil-*: we don't depend on Abseil; suggestions like absl::StrContains
#   would force a new dependency.
# * boost-*: we don't depend on Boost; suggestions like boost::range
#   would force a new dependency.
# * cppcoreguidelines-use-enum-class: invasive (~1000 sites), and
#   converting Liero's plain enums to scoped enums would break the
#   implicit int conversions threaded through serialization, weapon /
#   nobject tables, and SDL key/event handling.
# * cppcoreguidelines-special-member-functions / hicpp alias: requires
#   declaring the full rule-of-five on every type with a destructor,
#   producing >1000 boilerplate edits with no behavioural benefit.
# * cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-member-init: enforces default member
#   initialisers across ~1000 sites; touches POD types that are
#   memset-initialised or fully assigned by readers in serialization.
# * bugprone-implicit-widening-of-multiplication-result: false-positive
#   prone in graphics code where `int*int` widened to size_t is
#   intentional and safe.
# * google-explicit-constructor: prescriptive style preference; the
#   codebase relies on implicit conversions (e.g. fixed-point Scalar
#   from int literals) where adding `explicit` would force noisy casts
#   at hundreds of call sites.
# * misc-use-internal-linkage: gives false positives for functions
#   declared in `.hpp` and defined in `.cpp` whose only callers live in
#   other TUs (e.g. `GameEntry`, `CommonSave`). The check applies
#   `static` based on per-TU visibility and breaks the link step.
# * clang-analyzer-*: the path-sensitive static analyzer is noisy on
#   this codebase (false positives on raycasts, unread-final-stores in
#   tests, init-by-helper patterns). Running it under `scan-build` is a
#   separate workflow; the regular tidy pass should not gate on it.
# * cppcoreguidelines-virtual-class-destructor: the codebase uses
#   structs for data aggregates that happen to be inherited but are
#   never deleted through a base pointer. Forcing virtual destructors
#   would impose vtable overhead on hot paths (`Worm`, `NObject`).
# * misc-use-anonymous-namespace / llvm-prefer-static-over-anonymous-namespace:
#   stylistic preference between `static` and `namespace { }` for
#   internal linkage; not worth churning ~150 sites.
# * readability-function-cognitive-complexity: advisory only; the game
#   sim functions are inherently complex and rewriting them is out of
#   scope for a tidy flag day.
# * google-global-names-in-headers: flags `using std::vector` in
#   headers, which is intentional here for ergonomics.
# * google-runtime-int: prefers `int64_t` over `unsigned long`; the
#   codebase mixes SDL types and `cstdint`, so flagging every
#   `unsigned long` is noise.
# * fuchsia-multiple-inheritance / misc-multiple-inheritance: hits the
#   `FollowAI : WormAI, AiContext` pattern by design.
# * cppcoreguidelines-avoid-do-while: game loops use `do { } while`.
# * cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-const-cast: cereal's `serialize` path
#   const-casts when archiving non-const fields through a const archive.
# * bugprone-narrowing-conversions / cppcoreguidelines-narrowing-conversions:
#   pervasive in graphics/sound code where int<->uint8 is intentional.
# * cppcoreguidelines-avoid-goto / hicpp-avoid-goto: `common.cpp` uses
#   `goto fail` for the TGA reader's error-unwind chain.
# * concurrency-mt-unsafe: flags `localtime`, `strerror`, etc. We are
#   single-threaded outside the AI thread pool, which is documented.
# * modernize-use-std-print: requires C++23 `<print>` / `std::println`,
#   which the linux-x64-ci preset's local GCC has but CI's GCC 13 and
#   the macOS deployment target (pre-13.3 `std::format` runtime) do not.
#   Rewriting `printf` to `std::println` breaks the build on those
#   toolchains.
# * cppcoreguidelines-init-variables: auto-adds `= nullptr` to any
#   uninitialised variable, including platform-specific struct types
#   inside `#if _WIN32` blocks (e.g. `WIN32_FIND_DATAA scratch`) which
#   the local linux preset never compiles. False positives are
#   irrecoverable without per-platform manual review.
# * cert-err33-c: flags every `fprintf`/`printf` whose return value
#   isn't checked. The codebase uses these as fire-and-forget logging
#   on stderr (transport, signaling, replay-recording, online-connect,
#   tc/video tools); the check produces ~25 nuisance hits with no
#   actionable signal. Genuine "ignored return" bugs (fopen, fclose,
#   scanf, ...) are caught by the same family check
#   `bugprone-unused-return-value`, which stays enabled.
Checks: "*,\
  -google-readability-todo,\
  -altera-*,\
  -abseil-*,\
  -boost-*,\
  -cert-err33-c,\
  -clang-analyzer-*,\
  -concurrency-mt-unsafe,\
  -cppcoreguidelines-init-variables,\
  -modernize-use-std-print,\
  -fuchsia-*,\
  -llvm-header-guard,\
  -llvm-include-order,\
  -llvm-prefer-static-over-anonymous-namespace,\
  -llvmlibc-*,\
  -modernize-use-nodiscard,\
  -misc-multiple-inheritance,\
  -misc-non-private-member-variables-in-classes,\
  -misc-use-anonymous-namespace,\
  -misc-use-internal-linkage,\
  -readability-function-cognitive-complexity,\
  -readability-identifier-length,\
  -readability-magic-numbers,\
  -readability-braces-around-statements,\
  -readability-implicit-bool-conversion,\
  -readability-math-missing-parentheses,\
  -google-explicit-constructor,\
  -google-global-names-in-headers,\
  -google-readability-braces-around-statements,\
  -google-runtime-int,\
  -modernize-use-trailing-return-type,\
  -modernize-avoid-c-arrays,\
  -modernize-macro-to-enum,\
  -portability-avoid-pragma-once,\
  -misc-include-cleaner,\
  -bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters,\
  -bugprone-implicit-widening-of-multiplication-result,\
  -bugprone-narrowing-conversions,\
  -performance-enum-size,\
  -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-do-while,\
  -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-goto,\
  -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-magic-numbers,\
  -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-c-arrays,\
  -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-const-or-ref-data-members,\
  -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-non-const-global-variables,\
  -cppcoreguidelines-macro-usage,\
  -cppcoreguidelines-macro-to-enum,\
  -cppcoreguidelines-narrowing-conversions,\
  -cppcoreguidelines-non-private-member-variables-in-classes,\
  -cppcoreguidelines-owning-memory,\
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-array-to-pointer-decay,\
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-avoid-unchecked-container-access,\
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-constant-array-index,\
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-pointer-arithmetic,\
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-const-cast,\
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-member-init,\
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-reinterpret-cast,\
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-vararg,\
  -cppcoreguidelines-special-member-functions,\
  -cppcoreguidelines-use-enum-class,\
  -cppcoreguidelines-virtual-class-destructor,\
  -hicpp-avoid-goto,\
  -hicpp-avoid-c-arrays,\
  -hicpp-braces-around-statements,\
  -hicpp-explicit-conversions,\
  -hicpp-member-init,\
  -hicpp-named-parameter,\
  -hicpp-no-array-decay,\
  -hicpp-noexcept-move,\
  -hicpp-signed-bitwise,\
  -hicpp-special-member-functions,\
  -hicpp-uppercase-literal-suffix,\
  -hicpp-use-auto,\
  -hicpp-use-emplace,\
  -hicpp-use-equals-default,\
  -hicpp-use-nullptr,\
  -hicpp-use-override,\
  -hicpp-vararg"
# Lint warnings in our own headers (anything under src/) but not in
# third-party headers (SDL, cereal, vcpkg vendor code, system libs).
# Without this, tidy only reports warnings whose source location is in
# the .cpp being analyzed — inline code in headers goes unchecked.
HeaderFilterRegex: '.*/src/.*\.(h|hpp)$'
WarningsAsErrors: ''
CheckOptions:
  - key: 'bugprone-argument-comment.StrictMode'
    value: 'true'
# Prefer using enum classes with 2 values for parameters instead of bools
  - key: 'bugprone-argument-comment.CommentBoolLiterals'
    value: 'true'
  - key: 'bugprone-misplaced-widening-cast.CheckImplicitCasts'
    value: 'false'
  - key: 'bugprone-sizeof-expression.WarnOnSizeOfIntegerExpression'
    value: 'true'
  - key: 'bugprone-suspicious-string-compare.WarnOnLogicalNotComparison'
    value: 'true'
  - key: 'readability-simplify-boolean-expr.ChainedConditionalReturn'
    value: 'true'
  - key: 'readability-simplify-boolean-expr.ChainedConditionalAssignment'
    value: 'true'
  - key: 'readability-uniqueptr-delete-release.PreferResetCall'
    value: 'true'
  - key: 'cppcoreguidelines-init-variables.MathHeader'
    value: '<cmath>'
  - key: 'cppcoreguidelines-narrowing-conversions.PedanticMode'
    value: 'true'
  - key: 'readability-else-after-return.WarnOnUnfixable'
    value: 'true'
  - key: 'readability-else-after-return.WarnOnConditionVariables'
    value: 'true'
  - key: 'readability-inconsistent-declaration-parameter-name.Strict'
    value: 'true'
  - key: 'readability-qualified-auto.AddConstToQualified'
    value: 'true'
  - key: 'readability-redundant-access-specifiers.CheckFirstDeclaration'
    value: 'true'
# Identifier naming: Google C++ Style. Cereal ADL hooks (serialize,
# save, load, save_minimal, load_minimal) are carved out by regex —
# they are looked up by name via ADL, so renaming them would silently
# break serialization. The on-disk format uses explicit string literals
# in `cereal::make_nvp(...)`, so renaming the C++ fields does not
# change the save/snapshot format.
  - key: 'readability-identifier-naming.ClassCase'
    value: 'CamelCase'
  - key: 'readability-identifier-naming.StructCase'
    value: 'CamelCase'
  - key: 'readability-identifier-naming.EnumCase'
    value: 'CamelCase'
  - key: 'readability-identifier-naming.FunctionCase'
    value: 'CamelCase'
  - key: 'readability-identifier-naming.MethodCase'
    value: 'CamelCase'
  - key: 'readability-identifier-naming.VariableCase'
    value: 'lower_case'
  - key: 'readability-identifier-naming.ParameterCase'
    value: 'lower_case'
  - key: 'readability-identifier-naming.MemberCase'
    value: 'lower_case'
  - key: 'readability-identifier-naming.PrivateMemberSuffix'
    value: '_'
  - key: 'readability-identifier-naming.ProtectedMemberSuffix'
    value: '_'
  - key: 'readability-identifier-naming.ConstantCase'
    value: 'CamelCase'
  - key: 'readability-identifier-naming.ConstantPrefix'
    value: 'k'
  - key: 'readability-identifier-naming.EnumConstantCase'
    value: 'CamelCase'
  - key: 'readability-identifier-naming.EnumConstantPrefix'
    value: 'k'
  - key: 'readability-identifier-naming.MacroDefinitionCase'
    value: 'UPPER_CASE'
  - key: 'readability-identifier-naming.NamespaceCase'
    value: 'lower_case'
  - key: 'readability-identifier-naming.MethodIgnoredRegexp'
    value: '^(serialize|save|load|save_minimal|load_minimal|setNextName|startNode|finishNode|saveValue|loadValue|saveBinaryValue|loadBinaryValue|sizeTag)$'
  - key: 'readability-identifier-naming.FunctionIgnoredRegexp'
    value: '^(serialize|save|load|save_minimal|load_minimal|prologue|epilogue)$'
...
